Package net.ssehub.comani.analysis.deadcodechange.diff

Class FileDiff

java.lang.Object
net.ssehub.comani.analysis.deadcodechange.diff.FileDiff
Direct Known Subclasses:
BuildFileDiff, CodeFileDiff, VariabilityModelFileDiff
public abstract class FileDiff
extends java.lang.Object
This abstract class represents a general file diff. It implements common attributes and methods for the following sub-classes:
  • VariabilityModelFileDiff
  • BuildFileDiff
  • CodeFileDiff
Author:
Christian Kroeher

  • Constructor Details

    • FileDiff

      protected FileDiff​(FileDiff.FileType fileType, java.lang.String[] diffLines)
      Construct a new FileDiff.

      This constructor will start a line-wise analysis of the given diff lines calling the abstract methods normalize(String, int) and isRelevantChange(String, int). These methods are implemented in the specific file diff classes to detect changes to the variability information available in the specific type of file diff.
      Parameters:
      fileType - the FileDiff.FileType of this file diff
      diffLines - the full, line-wise diff description of a commit

  • Method Details

    • normalize

      protected abstract java.lang.String normalize​(java.lang.String diffLine, int diffLinePosition)
      Normalize the given diff line, e.g. remove leading "+" or "-", check if the line is a general comment or contains general comments as part of the line.
      Parameters:
      diffLine - the line of a diff description to be normalized
      diffLinePosition - the index of the given diff line in diffLines used, e.g., for backtracking
      Returns:
      the normalized diff line without leading "+" or "-"; in case of comments, only the non-comment part will be return, which may lead to an empty string

    • isRelevantChange

      protected abstract boolean isRelevantChange​(java.lang.String cleanDiffLine, int cleanDiffLinePosition)
      Check if the given diff line (without leading "+" or "-") describes a relevant change, which forces another dead code analysis.
      Parameters:
      cleanDiffLine - the line of a diff description to be checked for relevant change without leading "+" or "-"
      cleanDiffLinePosition - the index of the given diff line in diffLines used, e.g., for backtracking
      Returns:
      true if the given diff line contains variability information, false otherwise
